Nursery/ NICU Nurse
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/04 16:07:18
Ref. JB3047199
Job Description
On behalf of our client one of the leading Specialist Hospitals in Saudi Arabia we have an opening for a Nursery/ NICU Staff Nurse. Reporting to the Head Nurse.
Duties & Responsibilities
•	Collaborates with patient/ members of the health care team to develop and update a plan of care based on the patient's physical, psychological changes and age related requirements.
•	Transcribes physician's orders and reviews nursing and medical orders for accuracy and appropriateness.
•	Prepares, administers and documents the administration of all medications as prescribed by the physician.
•	Maintains accountability for narcotic and controlled drugs.
•	Intervenes appropriately in clinical emergency situations, initiates emergency resuscitative measures and assist with codes.
•	Ensures contact with the physicians for the purpose of reporting important information or clarifying orders.
•	Maintains a safe, clean and organized environment for the patient, family, visitors and staff.
•	Demonstrates priority setting and time liners in responding to patient needs.
•	Evaluates quality of nursing care being delivered and identifies opportunities for improvement.
•	Participates in presenting patient care conferences.
•	Establishes and maintains effective working relationship with other members of the health care team.
•	Maintains infection control and safety awareness functions accordingly and initiates corrective action when needed.
•	Acts as a role model for other staff members and ensures that all staff is maintaining professional behavior on duty.
•	Ensures the next shift receives a complete and pertinent report that facilitates continuity of care.
•	Participates in disaster drills and codes.
•	Uses verbal and non-verbal communication that conveys respect for the patient, family, visitors and staff.
•	Communicates verbal, written information in an accurate, concise and timely manner.
•	Receives baby delivered by NSVD or Caesarian Section.
•	Performs direct patient care to include resuscitation, giving Apgar score, cord clamping, bathing, vital statistics measurements, eye care, VS monitoring.
•	Assess and identifies newborn problems like RDS, TTN, Meconium Aspiration, Diaphragmatic Hernia, Hypoglycemia, Apnea to include babies with congenital abnormalities.
•	Sets up equipment and assists in doing special procedure like intubation and extubation, chest tube insertion, UAC/UVC insertion, lumbar tap, blood exchange transfusion.
•	Knowledgeable in the use of cardiac monitor, syringe pumps, infusion pumps, incubator, phototherapy, datascope, glucometer, transilluminator, O2 analyzer, suction apparatus and mechanical ventilator and Nasal CPAP.
•	Performs arterial puncture, IV insertion, blood extraction under aseptic technique.
•	Performs special procedure like NGT insertion, catheterization, suctioning, gastric lavage, gastric gavage and heel prick.
•	Accompanies in transporting sick babies to other health care facilities.
•	Gives health education to mothers regarding breastfeeding, hygiene, cord care, follow up clinic appointments, and vaccination schedule.
•	Vaccinates newborn with Hep. B and BCG.
•	Deals with babies’ pre and post circumcision.
Skills
Specialty Qualifications/ Professional Experience.
•	Baccalaureate degree in Nursing/ Diploma in Nursing.
•	Graduate from recognized college of nursing.
•	Registration in country of origin.
•	MOH License to work in KSA
•	Two years work experience
•	Training experience in NICU/Nursery
•	Completion of corresponding critical care course is preferred
•	Good command of English and Arabic preferred.
•	With a thorough knowledge, skills and techniques of good patient care, with adequate technical vocabulary .
•	BCLS licensed.
•	NRP Certified
